<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="FO3" checkit-title="Substitution for First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Use an appropriate substitution
      to show that all of the following ODEs may be transformed into
      the same linear ODE.
      (Do not fully solve these ODEs.)
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><m>-4 \, t^{10} + t {y'} = -3 \, t^{7} y + y</m></li>
        <li><m>4 \, t^{8} - 7 \, {y'} = 15 \, t^{7} + 21 \, t^{6} y + 5</m></li>
        <li><m>4 \, t^{8} y^{5} + 4 \, {y'} = 3 \, t^{6} y</m></li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = \frac{y}{t}</m>.</p></li>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = 5 \, t + 7 \, y</m>.</p></li>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = \frac{1}{y^{4}}</m>.</p></li>
    </ol>
      <p>
          All ODEs transform into
          <m>3 \, t^{6} u + {u'} = 4 \, t^{8}</m>.
      </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
